commit_list.message:
Simplified settings

All the settings are stored at the beginning of the program (after the
license), with a little description before them.

The management of settings should be improved: I want to destroy this
kind of section. "days", "hours" and "shift" should be stored in the
database, and it should be possible to edit them directly from the gui.
The location of the database should be asked from the gui too, adding
also a nice "recent files" menu.

In few words: actually there's no reason to have a settings file or a
part in the program where to save default settings; so I want to remove
them because I think that they are a workaround :)
commit_list.repo_description: A nice way to keep your weekly stuffs ordered :)

commit_list.message:
Initial commit

This is the first draft. The GUI is working, but it's very minimal.
There's no save or load actions for now, only a table and a simple
text editor, where you can write notes, like a legend.
commit_list.repo_description: A nice way to keep your weekly stuffs ordered :)

commit_list.message:
Fixed rows/columns index error

This error didn't allow you to store some informations.
commit_list.repo_description: A nice way to keep your weekly stuffs ordered :)

commit_list.message:
Code cleanup

Now the code is cleaner and easier to read. I've also put some comments
in order to let everyone know what I'm doing :)

Actually, only two changes are really important:
 * The old database it's not compatible with the current version,
   because the variable name is changed "table" is better than "datas")
 * In order to prevent problems, I changed the default database name
   from "orari.db" to the more internationalized name "agenda.db"
commit_list.repo_description: A nice way to keep your weekly stuffs ordered :)

commit_list.message:
Implemented save and load actions

Now you can keep your datas stored, by default, in "orari.db" and reload
them when you want :)

Keep in mind that it will not warn you about possible data loss if you
close the window without have saved them first.
